================================================================================
MEMETOK — FULL CODEBASE ANALYSIS & TODO
(Instagram Reels-style platform, upload-protected to selected users)
Generated: 2026-03-03
================================================================================

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 1: BUGS TO FIX
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[x] 1. SAVE STATE NOT PERSISTED ON LOAD (VideoSidebar.tsx)
    Problem: `isSaved` is local useState that starts as `false` always. When the
    user already saved a post and scrolls back, the bookmark icon reverts to
    unsaved state. The toggle endpoint works but the read state is never loaded.
    Fix: Add a `GET /posts/:id/saved` endpoint or return `savedByUser` flag in
    the post feed response, and initialize `isSaved` from it.

[x] 2. LIKED STATE NOT PERSISTED ACROSS SESSIONS (feedSlice.ts)
    Problem: `likedVideos[]` in Redux is in-memory only. Refreshing the page
    clears all liked state. The like count comes from the server (correct), but
    the heart icon state resets.
    Fix: On feed load, query a `GET /posts/liked?take=N` endpoint or embed
    `likedByUser: bool` in each post's feed response so the UI can pre-populate
    `likedVideos[]`.

[x] 3. STATS LOADED PER-CARD CAUSING N+1 REQUESTS (VideoSidebar.tsx)
    Problem: Every VideoCard/VideoSidebar component calls `fetchPostStats(video.id)`
    independently on mount via `useEffect`. With 10 visible posts, that's 10
    separate stats API requests on every feed load.
    Fix: Include `stats: { likes, comments }` in the LIST_POSTS response itself
    (remove `{\"stats\": 0}` projection from `find_latest_posted`). The `stats`
    field already lives on the post document. Eliminate the per-card stat fetch.

[x] 4. SAVED POSTS FETCHED ONE-BY-ONE (service.py)
    Problem: `list_saved_posts()` in PostsService iterates post_ids and calls
    `posts_repo.find_by_id()` for EACH one — classic N+1.
    Fix: Add `find_by_ids(post_ids: List[str])` to PostsRepository using
    `{\"id\": {\"$in\": post_ids}}` and batch-fetch all saved posts in one query.

[x] 5. PIPELINE READS ENTIRE FILE INTO MEMORY (pipeline.py)
    Problem: `_process_upload()` reads the full file into memory with
    `file_content = f.read()`, then uploads it. For large videos this doubles
    RAM usage: once on disk, once in memory.
    Fix: Stream the file to Streamlander using chunked reading or multipart
    streaming, avoiding the full in-memory buffer.

[x] 6. PIPELINE WORKERS NOT STARTED (api/index.py)
    Problem: `pipeline.start_workers(num_workers=2)` is NEVER called in the
    lifespan. The pipeline object is created via `get_shared_pipeline()`, but
    its workers are never launched and `pipeline.enqueue(context)` puts items
    in a queue that nobody processes.
    Fix: Add `pipeline.start_workers()` call inside the lifespan startup block.

[x] 7. UPLOADER DEACTIVATION NOT ENFORCED AT LIKE/COMMENT/SAVE LEVEL
    Problem: `toggle_like`, `add_comment`, `toggle_save_post` accept any
    `userId` string with no auth check whatsoever—handlers just trust the
    payload. Any client can forge a `userId` and like/comment as anyone.
    Fix: In handle_toggle_like, handle_add_comment, handle_toggle_save_post,
    verify `__auth` header is present and extract userId from the token, not
    from the raw payload.

[x] 8. COMMENT "REPLY" AND "LIKE" BUTTONS ARE NON-FUNCTIONAL (CommentDrawer.tsx)
    Problem: Comment heart icon and "Reply" button are rendered but do nothing.
    They have no onClick handlers. Users see interactive-looking buttons that
    are dead.
    Fix: Either wire them up to real endpoints, or hide them until the feature
    is implemented (don't show fake affordances).

[x] 9. FEED LOAD-MORE THRESHOLD IS WRONG (VideoFeed.tsx)
    Problem: `const threshold = videos.length - 1;` triggers loadMore only when
    AT the very last video. With `postsPerPage = 3`, there is no buffer — the
    user hits a dead end before the next batch arrives.
    Fix: Use `videos.length - 2` or `videos.length - 3` to pre-fetch before
    the user reaches the end.

[x] 10. API CLIENT TOKEN IS GLOBAL MUTABLE STATE (api-client.ts)
    Problem: `apiClient.setToken(token)` mutates a singleton's token field.
    If two concurrent requests are made (e.g. toggleLike + addComment), they may
    share a stale or wrong token.
    Fix: Pass the token per-request via request headers instead of storing it
    globally on the `ApiClient` instance. Or create request-scoped headers.

[x] 11. UPLOADER CREATE SILENTLY RETURNS EXISTING WITHOUT NEW API KEY (service.py)
    Problem: `create_uploader()` returns `(existing_uploader, None)` if the
    email already exists. The SuperAdmin page then shows no API key in the toast,
    confusing the admin who may think it worked.
    Fix: Return a clear `{"alreadyExists": true}` flag so the UI can show
    "Uploader already exists" instead of silently doing nothing.

[ ] 12. INTERSECTION OBSERVER NOT RE-APPLIED AFTER LOAD-MORE (VideoFeed.tsx)
    Problem: The IntersectionObserver is set up with `videos` in its dependency
    array. When new videos are appended, the observer disconnects and reconnects,
    but newly appended `.video-card` elements that were not in the DOM at the
    time of re-connection might be missed if renderConfigs changes simultaneously.
    Fix: Use a ResizeObserver / MutationObserver or re-observe only newly added
    cards. OR switch to IntersectionObserver on the scroll container with a
    sentinel element at the bottom instead of observing each card.

[ ] 13. UPLOAD PIPELINE DOES NOT CLEAN UP ON FAILED POST DB INSERT (controller.py)
    Problem: If `_svc.create_post(...)` succeeds but the pipeline enqueue fails
    (or if the Streamlander upload fails entirely), the post document remains in
    MongoDB with status="pending" and no media forever. There is no cleanup or
    retry logic for dangling pending posts.
    Fix: Add a background cleanup job that deletes or marks as "failed" any post
    older than N minutes that is still in "pending" status.

[ ] 14. NO DELETE POST FUNCTIONALITY
    Problem: Uploaders currently have no way to delete a post they uploaded.
    There is no `DELETE /posts/:id` handler registered in the handlers or in
    `PostsMutationAction`.
    Fix: Add a DELETE handler and endpoint that verifies the requesting uploader
    owns the post, removes it from MongoDB and cleans up media from Streamlander.

[ ] 15. SUPERADMIN KEY STORED IN sessionStorage (SuperAdmin.tsx)
    Problem: `sessionStorage.setItem("superAdminKey", key)` stores the plaintext
    super admin key in browser storage. This persists across tabs in the same
    session and is accessible via XSS.
    Fix: Keep the key only in React state (never persist it). Require the admin
    to re-enter the key on each session start.

[ ] 16. CACHE TTL — STALE DATA NEVER EXPIRES (cache.ts)
    Problem: IndexedDB cache for posts, stats, and comments has NO TTL or
    eviction strategy. Stats get increasingly stale (likes counted wrongly).
    Fix: Store a `cachedAt` timestamp alongside each cached item. On read, if
    `Date.now() - cachedAt > TTL_MS` treat it as a cache miss. Clear old DB
    entries periodically via `cache.cleanup()`.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 2: SECURITY HARDENING
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] 17. RATE LIMIT UPLOAD ENDPOINT
    Problem: `/api/posts/upload` has no rate limiting beyond the Semaphore of 1
    concurrent ingest per-process. A malicious uploader can spam uploads.
    Fix: Add per-uploader rate limiting (e.g. 5 uploads/hour using a Redis
    counter or simple in-memory dict keyed by uploader_id). Return 429 when
    exceeded.

[ ] 18. VALIDATE FILE MAGIC BYTES NOT JUST EXTENSION/CONTENT-TYPE
    Problem: `is_video` is determined by `content_type == "video/mp4"` or
    filename ends with `.mp4`. Both are trivially spoofed by a client.
    Fix: After saving to tmp, check the actual file magic bytes (first 12 bytes)
    using `python-magic` or `filetype` library to confirm it's a real MP4/image
    before passing it to the pipeline.

[ ] 19. LIKE/SAVE/COMMENT ENDPOINTS ACCEPT ARBITRARY USER IDS
    Problem: As noted in Bug #7 — the payload `userId` is trusted without
    server-side auth. This is a significant ownership bypass.
    Fix: Extract `userId` ONLY from the verified Clerk JWT via `__auth`,
    never from the raw payload.

[ ] 20. NO INPUT SANITIZATION ON COMMENT TEXT
    Problem: Comment text is stored and displayed as-is. While React escapes
    HTML by default, URLs and other content in comments are not validated.
    Fix: Strip control characters and limit to sensible Unicode ranges.
    Consider adding profanity/spam filtering as a post-processing step.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 3: PERFORMANCE IMPROVEMENTS (non-cache)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] 21. ADD MONGODB INDEXES
    The following queries run without confirmed indexes:
    - `posts.find({"status": "posted"})` → needs compound index on {status: 1, createdAt: -1}
    - `posts.find({"author.userId": uid})` → needs index on {author.userId: 1}
    - `likes.find({"postId": pid, "userId": uid})` → compound index {postId: 1, userId: 1}
    - `saved_posts.find({"userId": uid})` → index on {userId: 1, createdAt: -1}
    - `comments.find({"postId": pid})` → index on {postId: 1, createdAt: -1}
    Add `ensure_indexes()` method to each repository and call on startup.

[ ] 22. INCLUDE STATS IN FEED RESPONSE (ELIMINATE N+1)
    As noted in Bug #3: return `stats` inside each post document in
    `find_latest_posted`. This alone will eliminate 10+ extra HTTP requests
    per feed page load.

[ ] 23. PAGINATE COMMENTS LAZILY
    Problem: `listComments` fetches 50 comments at once even if the user never
    scrolls. Most users look at 5-10 comments.
    Fix: Load first 10 comments by default. Show a "Load more" button for the
    rest using skip/take pagination already in place.

[ ] 24. VIDEO PRELOADING STRATEGY IS AGGRESSIVE (useVideoPreload.ts)
    Problem: Next Up video (`distance === 1`) gets `preload="auto"` — meaning
    the browser downloads the entire next video while the current one plays.
    On mobile data this wastes bandwidth.
    Fix: Use `preload="metadata"` for `distance === 1` and only switch to
    `preload="auto"` when the user is within the last 10s of the current video.
    Use the `timeupdate` event on the active video to trigger this.

[ ] 25. INITIAL POSTS FETCHED IS ONLY 3 (appConfig.ts)
    `initialPostsToFetch: 3` and `postsPerPage: 3` means the first API call
    loads 3 posts, and then immediately triggers another load-more on the 2nd
    post. This causes an extra round-trip within the first few seconds.
    Fix: Raise `initialPostsToFetch` to 5–7 for the first render, and keep
    `postsPerPage` at 3 for subsequent loads.

[ ] 26. STREAMLANDER UPLOAD IS SYNCHRONOUS IN PIPELINE (pipeline.py)
    The pipeline uploads to Streamlander and THEN updates the post status.
    There is no timeout on the Streamlander upload call. A slow/stuck upload
    will hang the pipeline worker indefinitely.
    Fix: Add an `asyncio.wait_for(upload_call, timeout=120)` around the
    Streamlander upload and handle TimeoutError explicitly.

[ ] 27. USE HTTP/2 OR KEEP-ALIVE FOR API CALLS
    The frontend makes many small API calls (stats, comments, toggle-like) using
    `fetch()` with no connection reuse config. Modern browsers do reuse
    connections, but the proxy/nginx layer should enable HTTP/2.
    Fix: Ensure nginx is configured with `http2 on;` in the server block.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 4: MISSING FEATURES TO ADD
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] 28. SEARCH / HASHTAG DISCOVERY
    Users can't search by tag or keyword. Tags are stored but never queried.
    Add a search bar that queries a `GET /posts/search?q=memes&tag=cats`
    endpoint backed by a MongoDB text index on `caption`, `description`, `tags`.

[ ] 29. ANALYTICS DASHBOARD FOR UPLOADERS
    The analytics microservice collects events (views, likes, plays) but this
    data is completely hidden from uploaders. They have no way to see how their
    posts perform.
    Fix: Build an Uploader Analytics page at `/portal/analytics` that charts
    views-over-time, like-rate, and top-performing posts by calling the
    analytics microservice `/analytics` endpoint.

[ ] 30. POST DELETE / UNPUBLISH FOR UPLOADERS
    As noted in Bug #14, there is no delete or unpublish mechanism.
    Add a delete button in the UploaderPortal / UserProfile "My Posts" grid
    that calls a soft-delete endpoint (set status to "deleted").

[ ] 31. REPOST / SHARE TO FEED
    Users can share via the share icon (opens native share sheet), but there is
    no built-in "repost" or "duet" concept. For the Reels use case, this is a
    common engagement pattern. Optionally add a flat "share count" counter.

[ ] 32. PUSH NOTIFICATIONS / REAL-TIME UPDATES
    When someone comments or likes a post, the uploader has no notification.
    Add WebSocket support or Server-Sent Events (SSE) so uploaders see live
    engagement on their content. Use a lightweight Pub/Sub on the backend
    (e.g. in-process event bus already exists — extend it to push SSE events).

[ ] 33. FOLLOW / SUBSCRIBE TO UPLOADER
    Currently there is no concept of "following" an uploader. Every user sees
    the same chronological feed.
    Feature: Add a follow system (user_follows collection), and offer a "For You"
    tab (algorithmic) vs "Following" tab (only followed uploaders' posts).

[ ] 34. SCHEDULED UPLOADS
    Uploaders sometimes want to publish at a specific time. Add an optional
    `publishAt: datetime` field to the upload form and post creation API.
    The pipeline can set status="scheduled" and a cron job flips it to "posted"
    at the right time.

[ ] 35. VIDEO PROGRESS BAR / SEEK
    The video player has no progress bar or seek capability. Users cannot rewind
    or check duration.
    Fix: Add a subtle bottom progress bar (thin line) showing the video's
    current position relative to total duration. Tap to seek.

[ ] 36. SOUND DISC IS PURELY DECORATIVE (VideoSidebar.tsx)
    The animated music disc SVG suggests there is audio info (track, artist)
    but clicking it does nothing.
    Fix: Either show a "Now playing" track overlay (if audio metadata is
    available) or remove the music disc to avoid false affordance.

[ ] 37. REFRESH / PULL-TO-REFRESH
    On mobile, users expect to pull down at the top of the feed to load new
    posts. This is not implemented.
    Fix: Add a `touchstart`/`touchmove`/`touchend` listener on the feed
    container to detect an overscroll pull gesture and trigger `fetchFeed()`.

[ ] 38. KEYBOARD NAVIGATION (DESKTOP)
    Arrow Up/Down or J/K keys to navigate between posts is expected on desktop.
    Fix: Add a `keydown` event listener that calls `scroll` on the container or
    programmatically advances the `visibleVideoIndex`.

[ ] 39. UPLOADER PROFILE PAGE
    There is no public-facing uploader profile at `/uploader/:id` or
    `/u/:username`. Clicking an avatar currently goes nowhere.
    Fix: Create an Uploader public profile page showing their bio (to be added
    to the Uploader document) and all their published posts in a grid.

[ ] 40. REPORT / FLAG POST FEATURE
    There is no way to report inappropriate content. Essential for a public-
    facing platform.
    Fix: Add a kebab-menu (⋮) on each post with a "Report" option that sends
    a `POST /posts/:id/report` with a `reason` field. Store in a `reports`
    collection and surface in SuperAdmin.

[ ] 41. EDIT POST (CAPTION / TAGS) FOR UPLOADERS
    Uploaders cannot fix a typo in a caption after publishing.
    Fix: Add a `PATCH /posts/:id` endpoint that allows uploader to update
    caption, description, and tags (verify ownership before update).

[ ] 42. EMPTY STATE FOR FIRST-TIME USERS
    When a brand-new user opens the app and there are posts, fine. But if no
    posts exist, they just see "No posts yet." — no onboarding.
    Fix: Add an onboarding screen or animated empty state with a call-to-action
    depending on whether user is an uploader or regular viewer.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 5: CODE QUALITY & TECH DEBT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[x] 43. CONSOLE.LOG STATEMENTS LEFT IN PRODUCTION (VideoCard.tsx)
    Multiple `console.log` calls are in VideoCard.tsx (play attempts, buffer
    progress, etc.) that pollute the browser console in production.
    Fix: Remove or replace with a proper debug logger controlled by a
    `VITE_DEBUG=true` env flag.

[x] 44. TYPE SAFETY ON BACKEND API RESPONSES IS `any` (api-client.ts)
    Most `execute<any>` or `execute<{ items: any[] }>` calls ignore response
    shape. TypeScript provides no help here.
    Fix: Define proper response DTOs and make the execute function generic-typed
    against them.

[ ] 45. ANALYTICS MICROSERVICE NOT INTEGRATED IN FRONTEND
    The Go analytics service is running (events endpoint, rate limiter,
    middleware) but there is no call to it from the frontend for events like
    "post_view", "post_like", "post_comment", "share".
    Fix: Wire up frontend analytics calls to the microservice for all key
    user events (views already have debounce logic per conversation history).

[ ] 46. superAdminApi.listApiKeys RETURNS EMPTY ARRAY (api.ts)
    The `listApiKeys()` function returns `{ items: [] }` with a comment saying
    "return empty for now". If the SuperAdmin page ever relies on this, it will
    silently fail.
    Fix: Either remove the method entirely or implement it to return per-uploader
    API key metadata.

[ ] 47. PIPELINE_SHARED AND JOBS_SHARED ARE SEPARATE SINGLETONS — NO COORDINATION
    `get_shared_pipeline()` and `get_shared_jobs_service()` return independent
    singleton instances. They each create their own `PostsRepository` and
    `StreamlanderClient`. This means extra connection setup on startup.
    Fix: Pass shared instances from `lifespan()` through dependency injection
    rather than relying on separate module-level singletons.

[ ] 48. NO TESTS BEYOND PLACEHOLDER (src/test/)
    The test directory has files but coverage of core flows (upload, feed, auth)
    is absent. Critical paths like the uploader auth flow have no unit tests.
    Fix: Add pytest tests for backend handlers and vitest tests for frontend
    hooks (useVideoPreload, feedSlice reducers).

[x] 49. BACKEND PYTHON ENVIRONMENT USES DATETIME.UTCNOW() (uploaders/service.py)
    `datetime.utcnow()` is deprecated in Python 3.12+. The mongo_common uses
    a `now_utc()` helper but uploaders/service.py calls `datetime.utcnow()`
    directly.
    Fix: Replace all `datetime.utcnow()` with `now_utc()` from mongo_common
    (or `datetime.now(timezone.utc)`).

[ ] 50. PROFILE DATA IN POSTS IS SNAPSHOT-ONLY (service.py)
    When a post is created, `username` and `profilePhoto` are baked into the
    post document (`author.username`, `author.profilePhoto`). If an uploader
    updates their Clerk profile, all existing posts still show the old name/photo.
    Fix: Either store only `userId` in posts and resolve profile data at query
    time via a lightweight Clerk API call (or a local cache), or add a
    background job to sync uploader profile snapshots.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 6: INFRASTRUCTURE / DEVOPS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] 51. NO DOCKER HEALTHCHECK FOR BACKEND SERVICE
    The docker-compose for the backend has no `healthcheck:` block. Docker
    will show the container as "Up" even if FastAPI is crashing at startup.
    Fix: Add `healthcheck: test: ["CMD", "curl", "-f", "http://localhost:8000/health"]`

[x] 52. UPLOAD TEMP FILES NOT CLEANED ON SERVER RESTART
    If the server crashes mid-pipeline, temp files under `/tmp/memetok_uploads/`
    accumulate. There is no startup cleanup.
    Fix: On lifespan startup, scan and remove tmp dirs older than 1 hour.

[x] 53. PIPELINE WORKER COUNT IS HARDCODED TO 2 (pipeline.py)
    `start_workers(num_workers=2)` is not configurable. For high load, this
    should be tunable.
    Fix: Read `num_workers` from app settings (`settings.pipeline_workers`).

[ ] 54. NO GRACEFUL DEGRADATION WHEN ANALYTICS IS DOWN
    If the analytics microservice is unavailable, frontend fetch calls fail
    silently (the VideoPost uses try/catch and ignores). This is fine, but it
    should be logged and surfaced.

